title: Google\Cloud\Asset\V1\RelatedAsset
name: RelatedAsset
description:
An asset identifier in Google Cloud which contains its name, type and ancestors. An asset can be any resource in the Google Cloud resource hierarchy, a resource outside the Google Cloud resource hierarchy (such as Google Kubernetes Engine clusters and objects), or a policy (e.g. Cloud IAM policy).

See Supported asset types for more information.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.asset.v1.RelatedAsset

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.asset
params.description: The full name of the asset. Example: //compute.googleapis.com/projects/my_project_123/zones/zone1/instances/instance1 See Resource names for more information.

params.name: data.asset_type
params.description: The type of the asset. Example: compute.googleapis.com/Disk See Supported asset types for more information.

params.name: data.ancestors
params.description: The ancestors of an asset in Google Cloud resource hierarchy, represented as a list of relative resource names. An ancestry path starts with the closest ancestor in the hierarchy and ends at root. Example: ["projects/123456789", "folders/5432", "organizations/1234"]

params.name: data.relationship_type
params.description: The unique identifier of the relationship type. Example: INSTANCE_TO_INSTANCEGROUP
